# 🦁 Samson Vision — Cursor Context

## Identity
Samson Vision is a text-based visual language that lets any text-only LLM "see" images. It translates pixels into a SAMSON_VISION_PACK (SVP) — 13 fields of structured text.

## Quick commands
- Generate SVP: `python3 src/samson_vision.py assets/samson_pillars_crumbling.png --md`
- Run tests: `python3 test/run_tests.py && python3 test/test_integration.py`
- Core module: `src/samson_core.py` (8 ASCII styles)
- SVP generator: `src/samson_vision.py` (13-field output)

## Key constraints
- Pipeline is 0% AI — only numpy + OpenCV + Tesseract
- Coordinates always normalized 0-100, never raw pixels
- All user-facing output on stdout; stderr for decoration only
- PUBLIC/ is for GitHub; source code is in src/

## Tech stack
Python 3.10+, pillow, numpy, opencv-python-headless (optional), pytesseract (optional)
